column169: On 10/2/2024 at approximately 1245, Dangerous Goods Administration received a call from Employee 393838 at the ramp facility in Fort Worth,  reporting a dangerous goods spill.  The shipment consisted of one fiberboard box that contained 4 glass bottles of petroleum crude oil.  The package was damaged by mechanical equipment, resulting in one of the glass bottles breaking and spilling.   There is no secondary containment or positive closure.  The cushioning between the bottles was insufficient.  The broken glass and damaged outer package were placed in a salvage drum for proper disposal and the remaining bottles were placed in a separate drum, awaiting an amended Shipper's Declaration for futher transport.

The leaking drums were each placed into a 65-gallon poly overpack. Absorbents and simple green were utilized to clean and neutralize the impacted areas.
